data.description: You know you have found your forever home when you walk through the front door!  This home is warm, inviting and spacious.  The living room has beautiful wood floors, vaulted ceilings with a skylight, a pellet stove and a sliding glass door leading out to the totally private courtyard patio in your shady back yard.  The formal dining room has loads of light with South facing arched windows.  The kitchen continues the spacious theme with loads of counterspace, elevated sink, upgraded appliances, granite countertops, breakfast nook and French doors leading to your covered patio with an outdoor kitchen with a natural gas grill and heating drawers.  Your private primary suite features a large cedar lined walk-in closet, five-piece ensuite bath with vessel sinks, Jacuzzi tub and walk-in shower, plus you have your own door leading to the courtyard patio.  The other two bedrooms have walk-in closets and are separated by a full bathroom with a vessel sink.    The home is walking distance to Grand Mesa Middle School and Central High School.  The interior has been freshly painted and has paid-in-full solar.  The attached 3-car garage currently has a ramp the leads you to the laundry room with the large front load washer and dryer.  The Seller has had the home Verified for your peace of mind.  That means it has been pre-inspected for you AND you will have a one-year home warranty.
